# Backtest Safety

## No-lookahead rule

`date_to` must be strictly before today. Never feed future outcomes to the model.

## Calibration checklist (before GO)

- Avg Brier < 0.235
- All 8 stats show Brier improvement vs uncalibrated
- Minutes 35+ bucket bias < +/-3.0 min
- `models/prob_calibration.json` exists and `_fitted_at` < 60 days old
- `blk` and `fg3m` 60-80% bin gaps documented, NOT used as GO signals
- `reb` 60-70% bin gap < 12%

## Real-line backtest

Only trust runs where `realLineSamples > 0`. Judge model by `roiReal`, not blended/synthetic ROI. Synthetic-line ROI (+20-24%) is a calibration diagnostic, not a real-money estimate.

## Comparison protocol

Same date range, same books/stats, same odds DB. Compare `roiReal`, `hitRate` on real-line subset, and `realLineSamples` count only.

## GO-LIVE gate (paper_summary)

- `sample >= 30` settled signals
- `roi > 0.0`
- `positive_clv_pct >= 50.0`
- No single stat with >=20 signals AND hit rate < 45%
